-- No country should leave euro zone: OECD'S Gurria
-- 
-- Sun Sep 2, 2012 3:34am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/09/02/us-oecd-euro-idUSBRE88101H20120902

 

 BLED, Slovenia  (Reuters) - The euro zone will remain intact despite the current crisis, the secretary-general of the Organisation for Economic Cooperation and Development (OECD) said on Sunday. 
 "I believe nobody is going to leave the euro and nobody should leave the euro," Angel Gurria told a news conference during an international forum in Slovenia. (Reporting by Marja Novak; Writing by  Zoran Radosavljevic ; Editing by Pravin Char)